<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1169739296745">
<term>chain rule</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1169739296750">the chain rule defines the derivative of a composite function as the derivative of the outer function evaluated at the inner function times the derivative of the inner function</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
